When you see a search result (including on the labels page) for a page which contains an HTML macro, the raw macro contents (the HTML markup) is displayed instead of the text that a user would see when they viewed the page.

Ideally, the HTML macro would put just the text content of the macro into the index rather than the HTML code. This would show the summary as text on the search and label screens in Confluence.

